OL,3,CThe death of Pope Francis is a time of
OL,4,Csorrow, but also one of gratitude
OL,6,FAnd then I realised Pope Francis was
OL,7,Fheading to the empty chair next to me.
OL,9,FIn a mixture of sheer nerves and
OL,10,Fdelight I held out my hand to greet
OL,11,Fhim as he came towards me...in one of
OL,12,Fthose classic moments where it happens
OL,13,Fin slow motion and you can't quite
OL,14,Fbelieve it. I was grinning like an
OL,15,Fidiot, mangling my words.
OL,17,FAs a journalist and as a cradle,
OL,18,Fpractising Catholic - this was quite
OL,19,Fthe moment both professionally and
OL,20,Feven more so, personally.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
