OL,3,CThe death of Pope Francis is a time of
OL,4,Csorrow, but also one of gratitude
OL,6,FHe took my hands in his and simply
OL,7,Fsaid 'Senora' - and then gallantly
OL,8,Fheld down the pop-up seat of the chair
OL,9,Ffor me to sit back down, my knees
OL,10,Fknocking.
OL,12,FI caught Theresa May's eye. She was
OL,13,Fgrinning too.
OL,15,FIt was fascinating to watch him close
OL,16,Fup as he delivered his remarks. I
OL,17,Fmoved the microphone towards him.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
