OL,3,CThe death of Pope Francis is a time of
OL,4,Csorrow, but also one of gratitude
OL,6,FHe said: "It's a crime against
OL,7,Fhumanity. It's a form of slavery and
OL,8,Fas Christians, those who suffer are
OL,9,Fthe body of Christ, the flesh of
OL,10,FChrist.
OL,12,F"Humanity still hasn't learned how to
OL,13,Fcry, how to lament. We need many tears
OL,14,Fin order to understand the dimension
OL,15,Fof this drama."
OL,17,FWhen I thanked him again he shook my
OL,18,Fhand and said: "Pray for me".
