OL,3,CThe death of Pope Francis is a time of
OL,4,Csorrow, but also one of gratitude
OL,6,FFrancis was candid right from the
OL,7,Fbeginning of his papacy that the
OL,8,Fhighest honour and burden of the RC
OL,9,FChurch - the seat of St Peter - was in
OL,10,Fthe hands of a man who felt deeply the
OL,11,Frealities, limits, doubts and worries
OL,12,Fof every human being.
OL,14,FHe made the appeal "Pray for me" from
OL,15,Fhis hospital bed.
OL,17,FIn his deep faith, he will have been
OL,18,Fpreparing for this moment for many
OL,19,Fyears.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
